# Cursor Rules for cole_press

## Project Overview

Personal website at cole.press built with Quarto + R + SCSS.
Terminal/CLI-inspired design with monospace typography.

## Tech Stack

- Quarto ≥1.7.31 (static site generator)
- R ≥4.5.1 (code execution)
- SCSS (theming)
- TinyTeX (CV PDF generation)
- Netlify (deployment)

## Commands

```
make preview  - Dev server
make build    - Render site
make setup    - Install deps
make clean    - Clean generated files
```

## File Patterns

*.qmd       → Quarto Markdown content
*.scss      → Theme styling
_quarto.yml → Site configuration
*.tex       → LaTeX templates (CV)
*.lua       → Quarto filters

## Key Files

_quarto.yml             - Site config, navigation
monospatial-light.scss  - Primary theme
monospatial-dark.scss   - Dark mode overrides
_fonts.scss             - Font definitions
DESCRIPTION             - R dependencies

## Coding Style

### Quarto Markdown
- YAML front matter: title, date, description
- Icons: {{< fa icon-name >}}
- R chunks: ```{r} with #| options

### SCSS
- Monospace font: Anonymous Pro
- Terminal-inspired aesthetics
- CSS custom properties for colors
- Mobile-first responsive

### Configuration
- Follow Quarto YAML schema
- Navbar items: text + href

## Extensions

fontawesome - {{< fa brands github >}}
quarto-cv   - PDF CV generation

## Do Not

- Modify _extensions/ without request
- Use npm for rendering (only for Netlify plugin)
- Suggest full TeX Live (use TinyTeX)

